---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Bird Friendly Kitchener — Certified Bird Friendly City">
  <Header slot="header" currentPath="/kitchener" />

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Bird Friendly Kitchener</h1>
      <span class="status status-certified">✓ Certified Bird Friendly City — 2024</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="page-content">
    <p>
      In November 2024, Kitchener was officially certified as a
      <strong>Bird Friendly City</strong> by
      <a href="https://naturecanada.ca/defend-nature/how-you-help-us-take-action/bfc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nature Canada</a>,
      recognizing the city's commitment to reducing threats to birds,
      protecting and restoring habitats, and engaging the community.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Bird Friendly Kitchener team is a subcommittee of
      <a href="https://www.waterlooregionnature.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Waterloo Region Nature</a>,
      made up of dedicated community members including ecologists, educators, artists, and
      bird enthusiasts. We work cooperatively with the City of Kitchener, the University of Waterloo,
      and other community organizations.
    </p>

    <p>
      Our work focuses on addressing key threats to birds — including window collisions, habitat loss,
      pesticide use, and cat predation — while promoting bird-friendly practices across the community.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>More content coming soon.</strong> In the meantime, visit our current site at
      <a href="https://bfck.waterlooregionnature.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bfck.waterlooregionnature.ca</a>.
    </p>

    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to home</a>
  </div>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
